📝 Simple To-Do List App

A lightweight and responsive To-Do List built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
This app allows users to add and delete tasks dynamically, helping practice DOM manipulation and event handling.

🚀 Features

➕ Add new tasks easily

❌ Delete tasks with a single click

🎨 Clean and simple UI with hover effects

📱 Responsive design

🛠️ Technologies Used

HTML5 – structure of the app

CSS3 – styling and layout

JavaScript (Vanilla) – functionality & DOM manipulation

📸 Screenshot

(Add a screenshot of your app here — you can take one and save it as screenshot.png in your repo)

⚡ How to Run Locally

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/your-username/todo-list-app.git


Navigate into the project folder:

cd todo-list-app


Open index.html in your browser.

🌱 Future Improvements

Save tasks to local storage so they don’t disappear after refresh

Add a “mark as completed” feature

Implement edit task functionality

📚 What I Learned

Creating elements dynamically using document.createElement()

Appending and removing child nodes in the DOM

Using addEventListener() for interactive UI components

Basic CSS for styling forms, buttons, and lists